so I think they're discussing
whether or not to film tomorrow.

148
00:09:41,213 --> 00:09:43,649
I can't believe this is happening now.

149
00:09:44,450 --> 00:09:45,885
Seriously.

150
00:09:48,788 --> 00:09:52,858
{\an8}<i>Right before Hamada arrived
on location, he was with Shigeoka.</i>

151
00:09:52,925 --> 00:09:54,427
{\an8}JOHNNY'S WEST
DAIKI SHIGEOKA (29)

152
00:09:54,493 --> 00:09:57,563
I was on the same plane
going back with Hama-chan.

153
00:09:57,630 --> 00:09:59,699
I remember it vividly.

154
00:09:59,765 --> 00:10:02,201
He got in the manager's car.

155
00:10:03,336 --> 00:10:05,638
I told him,
"Good luck with the drama."

156
00:10:05,705 --> 00:10:10,810
Then the window of the car rolled down

157
00:10:10,876 --> 00:10:15,181
and he said to me,
"I shall be back!" and left.

158
00:10:16,148 --> 00:10:17,416
Things like that.

159
00:10:19,518 --> 00:10:22,288
I couldn't say something like that.

160
00:10:22,355 --> 00:10:27,126
I'd probably be a little sad.

161
00:10:27,193 --> 00:10:32,331
Filming a drama with a bad back
on a very tough schedule.

162
00:10:32,398 --> 00:10:34,200
I'd probably sulk a little

163
00:10:34,266 --> 00:10:37,737
and be moody because I'd feel restricted.

164
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:39,939
I'd definitely feel nervous.

165
00:10:40,006 --> 00:10:43,843
Despite all that, Hama-chan said,

166
00:10:43,909 --> 00:10:47,747
"I shall be back!"
as if nothing was wrong.

167
00:10:48,347 --> 00:10:51,951
I've gotten to know
such an awesome guy.

168
00:10:52,885 --> 00:10:56,756
That's what I seriously thought to myself.

169
00:10:56,822 --> 00:11:02,928
I have no problems
introducing Hama-chan to other people.

170
00:11:03,729 --> 00:11:06,499
Of course,
I could introduce the others too.

171
00:11:06,565 --> 00:11:11,003
But Hamada is special.

172
00:11:12,972 --> 00:11:16,442
It's like reading through sayings
and famous quotes.

173
00:11:17,043 --> 00:11:19,345
What's the one I like?

174
00:11:19,412 --> 00:11:23,482
"People who laugh during tough times
are the strongest."

175
00:11:23,549 --> 00:11:24,850
It's this quote.

176
00:11:24,917 --> 00:11:26,819
It's like...

177
00:11:26,886 --> 00:11:30,423
People who laugh
even though they're mad

178
00:11:30,489 --> 00:11:33,059
are stronger
than those who just get mad.

179
00:11:33,826 --> 00:11:37,997
It's okay to cry when you're sad,

180
00:11:38,798 --> 00:11:45,504
but I read that people who laugh when
they're sad are so much stronger.

181
00:11:46,772 --> 00:11:49,642
I think that's how
I developed my own habits.

182
00:11:51,177 --> 00:11:55,147
<i>And there's also this man who
takes care of and fights for the group.</i>

183
00:11:56,782 --> 00:11:58,317
