To make it onto the green
in one shot in Kawagoe,

193
00:12:45,397 --> 00:12:46,866
I'll need an eight or a nine...

194
00:12:46,932 --> 00:12:49,068
Let's go with eight. An 8-iron, please!

195
00:12:50,870 --> 00:12:52,271
Should I uncross my legs?

196
00:12:52,338 --> 00:12:53,472
The other way...

197
00:12:54,140 --> 00:12:55,474
Like this?

198
00:12:55,541 --> 00:12:57,376
You want to see the sneakers, huh?

199
00:12:57,443 --> 00:12:59,478
-It's not in frame.
-It's not?!

200
00:13:02,248 --> 00:13:07,586
I really don't like doing things in a rush
or workplaces that are tense.

201
00:13:07,653 --> 00:13:11,457
Everyone's having fun
chatting and working.

202
00:13:11,524 --> 00:13:13,392
Having fun is what matters the most.

203
00:13:15,127 --> 00:13:19,598
<i>What matters most to Kotaki are
good relations with the staff.</i>

204
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:22,535
<i>This applies to other workplaces too.</i>

205
00:13:23,669 --> 00:13:26,205
Is that a tour T-shirt?

206
00:13:26,272 --> 00:13:28,507
Yeah. A staff T-shirt?

207
00:13:28,574 --> 00:13:31,644
We're working hard
together as a team.

208
00:13:32,912 --> 00:13:34,346
And that includes the staff.

209
00:13:36,715 --> 00:13:37,883
That's why...

210
00:13:39,451 --> 00:13:43,189
I want to wear the same T-shirt
as everybody else during rehearsals.

211
00:13:45,124 --> 00:13:47,426
I want to have fun during rehearsals too.

212
00:13:49,428 --> 00:13:52,097
<i>Behind the scenes during rehearsals,</i>

213
00:13:52,164 --> 00:13:55,634
<i>he wears hoodies and T-shirts
meant for the staff.</i>

214
00:14:00,940 --> 00:14:05,377
{\an8}<i>In 2008, inspired by Hey! Say! JUMP's
Ryosuke Yamada,</i>

215
00:14:05,444 --> 00:14:08,280
{\an8}<i>Kotaki joined Johnny&Associates,Inc.
at the age of 12.</i>

216
00:14:10,482 --> 00:14:15,054
{\an8}<i>He was the youngest member in the group,
the only one to debut in his teens.</i>

217
00:14:16,155 --> 00:14:19,525
I'm always grateful
to the staff that supports us

218
00:14:19,592 --> 00:14:22,928
and the all the fans
who cheer us on.

219
00:14:22,995 --> 00:14:26,765
I'd like to repay everyone back.
Please continue to support us.

220
00:14:26,832 --> 00:14:29,435
{\an8}The way he thinks
is like a 35-year-old.

221
00:14:29,501 --> 00:14:30,669
{\an8}His thought process.

222
00:14:30,736 --> 00:14:31,737
{\an8}It's amazing.

223
00:14:31,804 --> 00:14:32,838
{\an8}TAKAHIRO HAMADA (32)

224
00:14:32,905 --> 00:14:36,375
{\an8}I think he's very mature.

225
00:14:38,010 --> 00:14:39,278
{\an8}Very sincere.

226
00:14:39,979 --> 00:14:43,949
