231
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:03,269
{\an8}SETAGAYA PUBLIC THEATRE

232
00:15:03,936 --> 00:15:05,471
{\an8}<i>For this play, Kotaki...</i>

233
00:15:05,537 --> 00:15:06,772
{\an8}BEST ACTOR & HARUKO SUGIMURA AWARD

234
00:15:06,839 --> 00:15:10,075
{\an8}I'm grateful to have had
the opportunity to play as Joseph Merrick.

235
00:15:10,142 --> 00:15:13,812
{\an8}And I'm thankful that
I was a part of this play.

236
00:15:14,880 --> 00:15:16,148
Hello there.

237
00:15:16,215 --> 00:15:18,083
Wow...

238
00:15:18,150 --> 00:15:22,121
"Should I be here?"
That's what I'm wondering.

239
00:15:22,187 --> 00:15:24,857
These people are
the cream of the crop.

240
00:15:25,658 --> 00:15:31,797
They're really the people at the top
of the theater community.

241
00:15:31,864 --> 00:15:34,533
And here I am. It felt quite strange.

242
00:15:35,567 --> 00:15:39,305
{\an8}<i>And this year, Kotaki will be part of
Agatha Christie's original play,</i>

243
00:15:39,371 --> 00:15:41,874
{\an8}The Witness for the Prosecution.

244
00:15:41,941 --> 00:15:45,844
I will be part of this play.

245
00:15:46,779 --> 00:15:48,113
Then...

246
00:15:49,782 --> 00:15:53,018
I'm going to do my best to perform
so people compliment me

247
00:15:53,085 --> 00:15:55,821
and can say that I was the best.

248
00:15:57,456 --> 00:15:59,358
That's how I feel.

249
00:16:01,226 --> 00:16:04,630
<i>What does JOHNNY'S WEST mean to him?</i>

250
00:16:08,701 --> 00:16:13,205
I didn't feel helpless then
nor did I feel lonely.

251
00:16:13,272 --> 00:16:15,741
But seeing them
after a long time was fun.

252
00:16:15,808 --> 00:16:22,114
That's when I'll realize for
the first time, "This is what I wanted."

253
00:16:24,249 --> 00:16:27,953
<i>And the group begins
to move in a new direction.</i>

254
00:16:28,554 --> 00:16:29,855
Yay!

255
00:16:32,224 --> 00:16:35,361
{\an8}Hamada's back is now
thoroughly healed in July.

256
00:16:35,427 --> 00:16:37,229
{\an8}JULY
<i>BUSHI-STANT AISAKAKUN!</i> FILMING

257
00:16:37,296 --> 00:16:38,764
{\an8}Cut!

258
00:16:40,265 --> 00:16:42,167
That's the end of this scene.

259
00:16:42,234 --> 00:16:43,802
Okay.

260
00:16:43,869 --> 00:16:44,903
-Oh?
-That means...

261
00:16:44,970 --> 00:16:46,405
What does it mean?

262
00:16:47,006 --> 00:16:51,176
-What does it mean?
-Sojiro Aisaka.

263
00:16:51,243 --> 00:16:53,045
Mr. Takahiro Hamada.

264
00:16:53,112 --> 00:16:54,680
Hey, hey!

265
00:16:54,747 --> 00:16:56,348
You're done filming!

266
00:16:56,415 --> 00:17:00,753
Good work.

267
00:17:00,819 --> 00:17:02,021
Thank you very much.

268
00:17:05,691 --> 00:17:06,925
Yeah!

269
00:17:08,260 --> 00:17:10,763
<i>The filming for the drama is now finished.</i>

270
00:17:10,829 --> 00:17:15,167
This was my first drama by myself.

271
00:17:15,234 --> 00:17:18,504
We wouldn't have been able to film

272
00:17:18,570 --> 00:17:21,740
such a good drama
without everyone's help.

273
00:17:21,807 --> 00:17:24,076
I truly believe this.

274
00:17:24,143 --> 00:17:26,678
I'm going to do my best to promote it!

275
00:17:31,650 --> 00:17:36,121
<i>There is one more piece
of good news about Hamada.</i>

276
00:17:37,956 --> 00:17:41,527
We're in charge of the theme songs
for the dramas we starred in.

277
00:17:42,428 --> 00:17:43,762
It doesn't usually happen.

278
00:17:43,829 --> 00:17:48,834
In the past, I would often ask,
"Can we have a tie-in with a song?"

279
00:17:48,901 --> 00:17:51,870
They'd be like, "no, no tie-ins."

280
00:17:51,937 --> 00:17:53,305
That's how it would be.

281
00:17:53,372 --> 00:17:56,975
I'd always ask just in case.

282
00:17:57,543 --> 00:17:58,877
I'm grateful.

283
00:17:58,944 --> 00:18:01,280
Oh, that's great.

284
00:18:01,346 --> 00:18:05,918
<i>Hamada's not the only one.
Shigeoka is also starring in a drama.</i>

285
00:18:09,154 --> 00:18:13,425
{\an8}<i>JOHNNY'S WEST is in charge of
the theme songs for both dramas.</i>

286
00:18:13,492 --> 00:18:16,562
{\an8}<i>BUSHI-STANT AISAKAKUN!</i> THEME SONG
"KIDOAIRAKU" MUSIC VIDEO

287
00:18:17,329 --> 00:18:19,098
<i>The theme song for Hamada's drama</i>

288
00:18:19,164 --> 00:18:22,334
<i>is a high-energy track
that works well with comedy.</i>

289
00:18:22,401 --> 00:18:23,769
"Kidoairaku."

290
00:18:24,870 --> 00:18:31,643
{\an8}"KIDOAIRAKU"

291
00:18:44,456 --> 00:18:50,729
{\an8}<i>On the other hand, in filming "Dekkai Ai,"
the theme song for Shigeoka's drama,</i>

292
00:18:50,796 --> 00:18:53,065
{\an8}<i>the group takes on
a certain new challenge.</i>

293
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:54,766
{\an8}"DEKKAI AI" MUSIC VIDEO

294
00:18:54,833 --> 00:18:57,870
{\an8}The whole thing will be
a bit mother-like.

295
00:18:57,936 --> 00:19:00,439
{\an8}You'll be doing the chores.

296
00:19:00,506 --> 00:19:04,343
{\an8}It's our first time doing this,
a music video where we don't sing.

297
00:19:04,409 --> 00:19:06,478
{\an8}It's the first time for our group.

298
00:19:06,545 --> 00:19:10,315
We're all excited
and nervous while filming.

299
00:19:11,250 --> 00:19:13,452
I have a question.
This is the setting, right?

300
00:19:13,519 --> 00:19:17,422
The doors connect here
but they're different places.

301
00:19:17,489 --> 00:19:19,124
-Yeah, it's all one house.
-Right?

302
00:19:19,191 --> 00:19:21,160
Can we talk here?
Or is that not allowed?

303
00:19:21,226 --> 00:19:25,330
Specifically speaking, it'd be interesting
if there was this kind of conversation.

304
00:19:26,632 --> 00:19:29,968
Just sweep normally like this.

305
00:19:31,236 --> 00:19:32,070
I got it.

306
00:19:32,137 --> 00:19:33,305
Cut!

307
00:19:33,372 --> 00:19:34,973
Sorry, that was an actual take.

308
00:19:35,040 --> 00:19:36,808
-Was that an actual take?
-Yes.

309
00:19:36,875 --> 00:19:38,944
-Sorry, I thought it was practice.
-Wow.

310
00:19:39,011 --> 00:19:40,746
-Can we do it again?
-Wow.

311
00:19:40,812 --> 00:19:42,281
Sorry, I should have been clearer.

312
00:19:42,347 --> 00:19:43,415
No, it was our fault!

313
00:19:43,482 --> 00:19:44,616
No, no, it's seven to three.

314
00:19:45,918 --> 00:19:48,153
Who's seven? Which is seven?

315
00:19:48,220 --> 00:19:49,955
I was looking elsewhere, wasn't I?

316
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:52,157
Shigeoka and I were looking
somewhere else.

317
00:19:52,224 --> 00:19:53,292
Shigeoka stands out.

318
00:19:53,358 --> 00:19:55,060
I wasn't looking at the right place.

319
00:19:55,127 --> 00:19:56,662
-Shall we do this?
-Let's do it.

320
00:19:56,728 --> 00:19:58,297
-Somebody should decide.
-Who?

321
00:20:00,165 --> 00:20:03,202
<i>The group's working hard
for this acting music video.</i>

322
00:20:04,469 --> 00:20:05,671
<i>Then...</i>

323
00:20:07,639 --> 00:20:14,646
{\an8}"DEKKAI AI"

324
00:20:23,088 --> 00:20:26,191
I was a lot of different dramas.

325
00:20:26,258 --> 00:20:30,128
Yeah, it was a lot of work.

326
00:20:30,829 --> 00:20:33,932
But I think this song is
truly perfect for it.

327
00:20:34,733 --> 00:20:40,072
I feel like this song somehow,
gives me courage in my life.

328
00:20:40,138 --> 00:20:45,444
I hope that we'll be able to
grow with this song.

329
00:20:47,012 --> 00:20:52,484
<i>The seven lights
will continue to shine more brightly.</i>

330
00:20:54,052 --> 00:20:55,921
<i>On the next</i> RIDE ON TIME<i>...</i>

331
00:20:56,588 --> 00:20:58,156
You surprised me.

332
00:20:58,223 --> 00:20:59,191
I'll go in now.

333
00:21:00,092 --> 00:21:02,694
<i>Nakama takes on the challenge
of being on the news.</i>

334
00:21:02,761 --> 00:21:03,929
<i>Also...</i>

335
00:21:04,596 --> 00:21:07,499
{\an8}There's no Japanese translation for that.
Don't you know that?

336
00:21:08,634 --> 00:21:11,703
{\an8}<i>Kiriyama challenges himself
in the theater as a chairman.</i>

337
00:21:11,770 --> 00:21:13,705
{\an8}<i>Here's what we discovered...</i>

338
00:21:14,806 --> 00:21:16,975
{\an8}If things continue like this...

339
00:21:17,976 --> 00:21:21,246
{\an8}I honestly might think of
doing other work.

340
00:21:21,313 --> 00:21:24,650
{\an8}If Mr. Johnny said "No," I'd have quit.

341
00:21:24,716 --> 00:21:26,485
{\an8}Junta told me he would too.

342
00:21:26,551 --> 00:21:27,786
{\an8}We both said the same thing.

343
00:21:27,853 --> 00:21:31,323
{\an8}"If you're not here,
then I don't need to do this."

344
00:21:32,190 --> 00:21:34,126
{\an8}<i>The strong emotions they don't show.</i>

345
00:21:35,594 --> 00:21:36,828
{\an8}Smile!

